cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to study the evolution of word meanings over time. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses word embeddings, which are a popular machine learning technique, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes statistical laws of semantic evolution, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with historical corpora, which could also fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
